# Contentrain CMS Content Management

When working with files in the `contentrain/` directory, follow these rules.

## Structure

```
contentrain.json                     # { "assetsPath": "contentrain/static" }
contentrain/
  assets.json                        # Asset registry
  models/
    metadata.json                    # Model list
    <modelId>.json                   # Field definitions per model
  <modelId>/
    <modelId>.json                   # Non-localized content
    <lang>.json                      # Localized content (en.json, tr.json)
```

## ID Format

12-character lowercase hex: `[a-f0-9]{12}` (e.g., `50d81f2a3baf`). Must be unique within a model and consistent across all locale files.

## System Fields (every content entry)

- `ID`: 12-char hex, set once
- `createdAt`: ISO 8601 string, set once, never modify on update
- `updatedAt`: ISO 8601 string, update on every edit
- `status`: `"draft"` | `"publish"` | `"changed"`

## Model Definition

`metadata.json` entry: `{ "name", "modelId", "localization", "type": "JSON"|"MD"|"MDX", "createdBy": "user", "isServerless": false }`

Field file (`models/<modelId>.json`): array of field objects. Must include 4 system fields (`createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `ID`, `status` with `"system": true`). MD/MDX models also need `slug` and `content` default fields.

## Component Types

- `string`: single-line-text, multi-line-text, email, url, slug, color, json, md-editor, rich-text-editor
- `number`: integer, decimal, rating, percent
- `number` but stored as `string`: phone-number
- `boolean`: checkbox, switch
- `date`: date, date-time (stored as ISO string)
- `media`: media (stores asset path string)
- `relation`: one-to-one (string ID), one-to-many (string[] IDs)

## Relations

```json
{ "options": { "reference": { "value": true, "form": { "reference": { "value": "<target-modelId>" } } } } }
```

## MD/MDX Rules

- JSON index: all fields EXCEPT body content
- Markdown file: YAML frontmatter + body
- Never store content body in JSON index
- Path: `<model.path>/<slug>.md` or `<model.path>/<lang>/<slug>.md`

## Assets

File: `contentrain/assets.json` (NOT `asset.json`). Physical file must exist at `path`. Media fields store the path string.

## Environment Branches

- `contentrain` = default
- `contentrain-<name>` = named environments (staging, production)

## Validation

- Valid JSON, no trailing commas
- All IDs: 12-char hex, unique
- Required fields present
- Relations reference existing entries
- Media paths in assets.json
- Localized entries: same ID across all locale files
- createdAt never modified on update
